1. INTRODUCTION
1.1 Preamble
In a rapidly changing world, working professionals are required to continually upgrade their knowledge
and keep up with the latest developments in diverse fields in order to be effective and remain relevant.
To meet such needs of the industry professionals, online certification programs all over the world have
grown rapidly in the last decade and have matured into formal degree-granting programs in many
Universities in USA and Europe. Several top-ranking universities like Stanford, UC Berkeley, Purdue,
UCLA, USC in the USA and Imperial, Warwick in UK have already started offering formal online
degree programs. Since there exists a large and growing ecosystem in India for online learning and
certification, and since there is a great demand from working professionals for such quality programs
in contemporary disciplines, it has, therefore, become imperative for practicing professionals to have
access to a complete ecosystem of knowledge. The eMasters program of IIT Kanpur has been designed
to fulfil this requirement. Given the high reputation of IIT Kanpur in its teaching and evaluation
standards, these formal degree courses with its intended high quality and standard will help
professionals in their vertical carrier growth and improve their employment potential during a later
movement.
1.2 eMasters Program
eMasters is a new graduate-level program at IIT Kanpur. It is a completely online program, with all
lectures, discussions, quizzes and assignments available through a professionally designed learning
management system. The course content will be delivered by the faculty of IIT Kanpur. The program
offers several flexible tracks, with multi-disciplinary modules, to facilitate learning for the professional.
All modules are designed to be intellectually challenging and state-of-the-art – the hallmark of IIT
Kanpur. eMasters is not equivalent to an MTech program nor it is an online version of MTech. A
mention of this will be made on the final transcript given to the graduating student and at other
appropriate places. Unlike MTech, eMasters does not have a thesis component and the structure and
nature of the courses may be different from those of MTech. It can be considered as a work-integrated
program since professional experience in the relevant areas are considered for admission into the
program.
2. ADMISSIONS
2.1 Eligibility for Admission
Bachelor's degree (4 years program) or a Master’s degree in appropriate discipline with at least
55% marks or 5.5/10 CPI + 2 years of work experience (an applicant need not be employed to
be eligible). Candidates with relevant experience will be preferred.
2.2 Admission Calendar
Admissions may be offered twice a year. Some programs may admit students once a year only.
The admission process is to be held during Feb - April and optionally during Oct-Dec.

538 E-MEETING OF SENATE
2.3 Admission Procedure
The admission process will be as follows:
• Admission process will be as rigorous as the admission process in our graduate programs and
will happen in multiple phases.
• Shortlisting will be based on certain minimum criteria as mentioned in the Senate Online
Program Committee (SOPC) Manual.
• An admission test designed to thoroughly evaluate the applicant’s domain knowledge and
competence will be conducted by IIT Kanpur.
• Admission test will be followed by an interview conducted by a departmental committee. An
admission committee for each program will be constituted by the Convener, Departmental
Online Program Committee (all participating Departmental Online Program Conveners, in
case of multi-department programs) and will be approved by Chairman, Senate Online
Program Committee.
• It will be ensured that only professionals from authentic and reputed
companies/organizations will be shortlisted for consideration to the program.
3. ACADEMICS
3.1 Academic Year
An academic year is divided into four quarters; each quarter is of 10 weeks duration. The
following is an example academic year with four quarters
• 1st Quarter: August to October
• 2nd Quarter: November to January
• 3rd Quarter: February to April
• 4th Quarter: May to July
3.2 Program Structure
The generic program template to be filled in by departments offering the eMasters program is
illustrated in the Table 1. Each teaching unit in a quarter is defined as a module. A module entails
8 weeks of teaching followed by an examination period of 2 weeks. Each Module will carry 5
credits.

There are two types of modules- core and electives. A program may have a set of core modules
defined that are compulsory and a set of modules as electives. A student must take all core modules
and obtain a grade other than X. A student must take sufficient electives to fulfil the credit
requirements for the program. For courses requiring pre-announced laboratory component,
students may be required to be present on campus, for a pre-defined period. Teaching material for
week one will be made available to admitted students at least eight weeks prior to commencement
of each quarter to facilitate selection of modules.
3.3 Program Registration
An admitted student registers for the program once at the beginning of the program. Program
registration is valid for three years. A student may apply to extend the program registration if
he/she has not completed all requirements of the program. A student is required to register for
every module that he/she plans to take in a quarter. Students must register during the registration
period for the selected modules subject to credit load constraints. There will be no provision to
add/drop modules. The registration process involves submitting a duly approved module/s
registration form for the quarter and payment of fees for the quarter and clearance of any
outstanding dues
3.4 Academic Requirements
The minimum duration of the program will be 4 quarters, and the maximum duration will be 12
quarters. A student must earn 60 credits to get an eMasters degree. All students will undergo a
mandatory contact program of 15 days with IIT Kanpur since the association with IIT Kanpur is
an important part of any degree program offered by IIT Kanpur
3.5 Load Requirements
Minimum duration for the program is 4 quarters, and maximum duration will be 12 quarters.
Normal load per quarter is 15 credits where each Module is of 5 credits. Each module will be of
10 weeks’ duration: the first 8 weeks will be used for teaching and exams will be held in 9/10 week.
A student may opt for 0, 5, 10 or 15 credits in a quarter, depending on his/her professional work
load, as long as they have registered for the program and paid the fee for each quarter - thus there
is no minimum load requirement. Overload may be permitted by the Departmental Online
Program Committee up to a maximum of 4 modules in exceptional circumstances.

538 E-MEETING OF SENATE
3.6 Academic Advising
Relevant member of the DOPC representing that particular program will serve as an academic
adviser. In case of a multi-department program, one of the relevant members for that particular
program, will be designated as an academic adviser by all participating Departmental Conveners.
3.7 Graduation Requirements
A student should have completed 60 credits, earned a minimum CPI of 6.5, paid all the dues to
the Institute, and should have no pending cases of indiscipline against him/her to graduate.
3.8 Credit Transfer
Some of these students graduating from the eMasters may subsequently wish to join other programs
like MTech or PhD at IIT Kanpur after going through the regular admission process and subject to
fulfilling the eligibility requirements as specified by the respective programs. If admitted, a student
with an eMasters degree may request for a waiver of up to 60 credits of coursework during
MTech/PhD programs and a waiver of two semesters of residential requirements to the Senate Post-
graduate Committee through the Departmental Post Graduate Committee. The credit transfer will be
approved by the Senate Post-Graduate Committee as per the prevailing PG Manual.
4. EVALUATION
4.1 Module Evaluation
The module evaluation policies (attendance, grading, marks distribution etc.) need to be
announced prior to the commencement of a module in that particular quarter. The evaluation
process will be designed to ensure that the high standards of IIT Kanpur processes are maintained.
A continuous mode of evaluation will be followed with online assessments like in video quizzes,
tests, and mid-quarter examination. The end-of-quarter proctored examination will be conducted
at pre-designated centers where the students appear in person and validate their identity to take
the examination.

4.3 Grading Structure
Seven letter grades: A*, A, B, C, D, E, F can be awarded. The correspondence between grades and
points (on a 10-point scale) is as follows:
A*: 10, A: 10, B: 8. C: 6, D: 4, E: 2. F: 0
In every registered module, a student is awarded one of the letter grades indicating his/her overall
performance in the module and earns 5 credits except when awarded grade is F in which case no
credits are earned. If a student does not complete sufficient requirements for a module, the
instructor may award grade I (Incomplete). The student must complete the module requirements
within 2 quarters. Then the instructor must convert an I grade to a regular letter grade, failing which
it will be automatically converted to an F grade. A student getting an E or a F grade in a module
must either repeat it or substitute it by another module as suggested by DOPC. A student getting a
D grade in a module may be allowed to repeat it.
The minimum CPI requirement for continuing in the programme or for graduation will be 6.5.
5. GOVERNANCE
5.1 Department Online Program Committee (DOPC)
Each participating Department/IDP constitutes this committee that consists of a Convener
from amongst the members representing different programs offered by the Department,
nominated by the Head of the department (in consultation with the faculty of the department),
Head of the department, and as many members of the faculty as necessary for different
programs offered by the Department. The tenure of the committee is one year. The DOPC
advises the students about their curriculum and handles any problem faced by students in their
academic program
AP-34
538 E-MEETING OF SENATE
5.2 Senate Online Program Committee (SOPC)
Senate Online Program Committee (SOPC) will consist of the following members:
• DOPC Conveners from participating departments/IDPs
• Two Nominees of the Senate
• Head CCE as a special invitee
A Chairman is elected amongst the DOPCs whose tenure is one year.
SOPC will operate through the DOPC to administer all academic aspects of the eMasters
program. SOPC while approving a Program, will consider the program completion requirements
and offering of appropriate courses.
5.3 Record Keeping
The record keeping of all documents related to the eMasters program will be done and managed
by the Dean of Academic Affairs (DOAA) Office.

knowledge and keep up with the latest developments in diverse fields in order to be effective and
remain relevant. To meet such needs of the industry professionals, online certification programs
all over the world have grown rapidly in the last decade and have matured into formal degree-

The eMasters program of IIT Kanpur has been designed to fulfil this requirement. Given the high
reputation of IIT Kanpur in its teaching and evaluation standards, these formal degree courses
with its intended high quality and standard will help professionals in their vertical carrier growth
and improve their employment potential during a later movement.
eMasters (eMS) Program
eMasters is a new graduate-level program at IIT Kanpur. It is a completely online program, with
all lectures, discussions, quizzes and assignments available through a professionally designed
learning management system. The course content will be delivered by the faculty of IIT Kanpur.
The program offers several flexible tracks, with multi-disciplinary modules, to facilitate learning
for the professional. All modules are designed to be intellectually challenging and state-of-the-

thesis component and the structure and nature of the courses may be different from those of
MTech. It can be considered as a work-integrated program since professional experience in the

Academics
Contact Program
All students will undergo a mandatory contact program of 15 days with IIT Kanpur since the
association with the IIT Kanpur campus is an important part of any degree program offered by IIT
Kanpur.
Intellectual Property Issues
All material generated will be considered Intellectual Property and appropriately protected
through IIT Kanpur’s IPR Cell. The learning platform, video lectures and the reading materials will
also display statutory warning on the copyright infringement. The Institute would also periodically
monitor for copyright infringement, if any.
Evaluation
The assessment process will be designed to ensure that the high standards of IIT Kanpur
admission process are maintained. A continuous mode of evaluation will be followed with online
assessments like in video quizzes, tests, and mid-quarter examination. The end-of-quarter
proctored examination will be conducted at pre-designated centers where the students appear
in person and validate their identity to take the examination.

Minimum duration for the program is 4 quarters, and maximum duration will be 12 quarters.

Online Program Committee up to a maximum of 4 modules in exceptional circumstances.

Credit Requirements
Each module is equivalent to 5 credits. The credit requirement to earn an eMasters is 60 credits

Credit Transfer
Some of these students graduating from the eMasters may subsequently wish to join other
programs like MTech or PhD at IIT Kanpur after going through the regular admission process and
subject to fulfilling the eligibility requirements as specified by the respective programs. If

Example Disciplines
The program can be offered by any department on approval by SOPC and Senate. Some example
disciplines are Data Science, Cyber Security, Financial Engineering, Telecommunications, Power
Sector Regulation Economics and Management.
Economic Viability
The fee structure will be such that the program will not only be self-sufficient but also will
generate revenue to the Institute.
